    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-12T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-12T11:00:00-05:00" n="801"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00 Statement July 16, 1937/180a:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-12T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 12, 1937—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>373. On Sunday morning next<note n="24" xml:id="d801fn24">August 15.</note> we
                    are publishing a series of comments from governments on the Secretary’s
                    statement of July 16, which was contained in radio bulletin No. 164 of that
                    date.</p>
                <pb facs="0793" n="781" xml:id="pg_781"/>
                <p>We have discussed the matter with Ambassador de los Rios, who concurs in our hope
                    that we will be able to include a message of endorsement of these principles
                    from the Spanish Government. To do this it will be necessary for us to receive
                    such a message at the latest by noon Saturday; I fear that if it were published
                    at a later date it would be less effective than if included with the replies of
                    probably 50 other nations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
